<%= form_for(@program_enrollment) do |f| %>
  <%= render 'shared/error_messages', object: f.object %>

  <%= f.label :study_program_id, "Study Program" %>
  <% study_programs = StudyProgram.where("school_id = ? and id != ?", current_school_user.school_id, 4) %>
  <%= f.collection_select(:study_program_id, study_programs, :id, :title_with_price) %>

  <%= hidden_field_tag :school_user_id, current_school_user.id %>

<center>
  <h1><%= @school.name %></h1>
  <h2><%= @school.address %>, <%= @school.city %>, WA <%= @school.zipcode %></h2>
  <h2><%= @school.email %> | <%= @school.phone %></h2>
</center>

<h1>Conditions</h1>
<p>
As a condition of acceptance as a student at <%= @school.name %>, I agree to the following conditions:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Training is to be satisfactorily completed as per this agreement within 12 months of the date of enrollment.  
      If the training is not satisfactorily completed, I will pay an additional $100 per month until all requirements are met.</li>

  <li>I will be issued a student kit as outlined in the school catalog.  I understand that the said student kit becomes 
      my property and it is not refundable after three school days from the date of this contract.</li>

  <li>I understand that no responsibility is assumed by the school for any negligence, carelessness or 
      lack of skill by one or more students while applicants practice any part of the school course upon one another.</li>

  <li>I further agree to strictly follow the rules and regulations of the school.  Failure to do so may result
      in suspension or dismissal with termination of training and any balance then due under this contract 
      will become due and payable as provided in paragraph (5) below.  Such suspension or dismissal shall be at the 
      sole discretion of the school.
  </li>
  <li>For students who enroll in the beginning classes, the following schedule of tuition adjustment is based 
      on the first day of class and either of the following dates:
    <ul>
      <li>The date of the student's last, physical presence/attendance in the school.</li>
      <li>The date of the student's formal cancellation initiated by the student.</li>
      <li>The date of dismissal or termination by the school.</li>
      <li>In case of leave of absence, the last day of physical attendance of the student.  
          Leave of absence can't be more than 14 school days.</li>
    </ul>  
  </li>
  <li>
    An applicant who is not accepted by the school shall be entitled to a refund of all monies paid.
  </li>
  <li>
    If a student cancels his or her enrollment within three business days after signing but prior to the first day of class,
    a refund of all monies paid to the school will be returned to the student less a registration or enrollment fee of $50.00.
  </li>
  <li>
    If the school is permanently closed and no longer offers instruction after a student enrolled, the student 
    shall be entitled to a pro-rate refund of tuition.
  </li>
  	<li>
      If a course is cancelled subsequent to a student's enrollment, the school shall at its option:  
      <ol>
        <li>Provide a full refund of all monies paid.</li>
        <li>Provide completion of the course.</li>
      </ol>
    </li>
  <li>
    I understand that in cases of prolonged illness or accident, death in the family or other circumstances 
    that make it impractical to complete the course, the school shall make a settlement which is reasonable and fair to both.
  </li>
  <li>
    I understand that the school does not guarantee employment upon passing the Washington State Board's exams.
  </li>
</ol>

<h1>Refund</h1>
